  <div class="story_text">
    <p>This policy explains our information practices, defines your privacy options and describes how your information is collected and used.</p>
    <p>By using visiting the Wayfare News Website, you agree to the collection and use of information in the manner described in this policy. Wayfare News shall have right at any time and without prior notice, at its sole discretion, to revise this policy. If we make material changes to this policy, we will notify you at this Wayfare News Website, by email, by means of a notice the next time you log in to the Wayfare News Website, or by means of a notice on the Wayfare News Website homepage. Such revisions and additions shall be effective immediately. You are responsible for reviewing the Wayfare News Website periodically for any modification to this policy. Any access or use of the Wayfare News Website by you after notice of modifications to this policy shall constitute and be deemed to be your agreement to such modifications.</p>

    <div class="legend">Information Collected and Information Provided</div>
    <p>This policy applies to all information collected by Wayfare News on the Wayfare News Website and any information you submit to Wayfare News or post to the Wayfare News Website. You will most likely provide us personal information to us when you register as a user of Wayfare News Website, when you use the Wayfare News Website or when you participate in certain Wayfare News promotions or events. The personal information we may collect includes: the information you submit to Wayfare News or post to the Wayfare News website, your name, passwords, user names, addresses, email addresses, and phone numbers.</p>

    <div class="legend">Your Information</div>
    <p>The Wayfare News Website lets you collect, submit, manage and share information about your interests. You can elect to share the information you collect and then post to the Wayfare News Website with others. In addition, the Wayfare News Website may include message areas that allow users to post or send information to the Wayfare News Website. When you post information to the Wayfare News Website, other site visitors can also view that information. We urge you to exercise caution when providing personally identifiable information to Wayfare News or the Wayfare News Website.</p>

    <div class="legend">How We Use Information</div>
    <p>Our primary goal in collecting your information is to provide you with a personalized, relevant, and positive experience with the Wayfare News Website.</p>
    <p>You can register on the Wayfare News Website to receive promotions and updates, or to be contacted for market research purposes. You can control your privacy preferences regarding such marketing communications (see the section below entitled "Your Privacy Preferences").</p>
    <p>From time to time, you may be invited to participate in optional customer surveys or promotions, and Wayfare News may request that you provide some or all of the above listed personal information in those surveys or promotions. We use information collected from surveys and promotions to learn about our customers in order to improve our services and develop new products and services of interest to our customers.</p>
    <p>In addition to the personal information you supply, we may collect certain information to evaluate how visitors, guests, and customers use the Wayfare News Website. We collect data to make the Wayfare News Website work better for you in the following ways: to improve the design of the Wayfare News Website, to provide personalization on the Wayfare News Website and to evaluate the performance of our marketing programs. The technologies we may use to gather this non-personal information may include "IP" addresses, "cookies", browser detection, and "weblogs".</p>
    <p>IP addresses define the Internet location of computers and help us better understand the geographic distribution of our visitors and customers and manage the performance of the Wayfare News Website. Cookies are tiny files placed onto the hard drive of your computer when you visit the Wayfare News Website, so we can immediately recognize you when you return to the Wayfare News Website and deliver content specific to your interests. You may modify your browser preferences to accept all cookies, be notified when a cookie is set, or reject all cookies. Please consult your browser instructions for information on how to modify your choices about cookies. If you modify your browser preferences, certain features of the Wayfare News Website may not be available to you.</p>
    <p>We may detect the type of web browser you are using to optimize the performance of the Wayfare News Website and to understand the mix of browsers used by our visitors, guests, and customers. To learn about how people use our site, we examine weblogs, which show the paths people take through the Wayfare News Website and how long they spend in certain areas.</p>
    <p>Wayfare News may contract with unaffiliated third parties to provide services such as customer communications, website analytics and other services. When we do this, we may provide your personally identifiable information to third parties only to provide those services, and they are not authorized to use your personally identifiable information for any other purpose.</p>

    <div class="legend">Our Commitment to Data Security</div>
    <p>Access to your data is limited to authorized Wayfare News staff or approved vendors. Although total security does not exist on the Internet, Wayfare News shall make commercially reasonable efforts to safeguard the information that you submit to Wayfare News or that Wayfare News collects.</p>

    <div class="legend">Use of the Wayfare News Website by Children</div>
    <p>The Wayfare News Website is not intended for use by children under the age of 13.</p>

    <div class="legend">Your Privacy Preferences</div>
    <p>When you sign up as a registered user of the Wayfare News Website you may begin receiving marketing communications such as e-mail newsletters, product and service updates and promotions. Our customers generally find this type of information useful. If you do not want to receive these updates, you must "opt-out" after registering. You can use any of the following methods to "opt-out": select the "unsubscribe" link at the bottom of any email communication and follow the opt-out instructions or send an email to unsubscribe@wayfare.io.</p>

    <div class="legend">How to Access or Correct Your Information</div>
    <p>You can access and maintain your personally identifiable information that we collect by sending us an email to privacy@wayfare.io. To protect your privacy and security, we require a user ID and password to verify your identity before granting access or making corrections to such personally identifiable information.</p>

    <div class="legend">Disclosure of Information</div>
    <p>You can use the Wayfare News Website to share the information you collect, submit and manage at the Wayfare News Website.</p>
    <p>We reserve the right to disclose your personally identifiable information as required by law and when we believe that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights and/or comply with a judicial proceeding, court order or legal process. It is also possible that Wayfare News would sell the company or all or substantially all of its assets. In any transaction of this kind, customer information, including your personally identifiable information, may be among the assets that are transferred. If we decide to so transfer your personally identifiable information, you will be notified by an email sent to the last known email address in our files and/or by notice posted on the Wayfare News Website.</p>

    <div class="legend">Privacy and other Websites</div>
    <p>The Wayfare News Website may contain links to other websites. Wayfare News is not responsible for the privacy practices of these other sites. We encourage you to be aware when you leave our site, and to read the privacy statements of each web site that collects personally identifiable information. Some linked sites may be co-branded with our trademarks and those of our business partners. They may have the look and feel of news.wayfare.io, but the URL in your browser window will indicate that you are visiting a different site. This policy only applies to information collected by Wayfare News.</p>
